<style>
.spf-switch-outerwrap {
  margin-top: 20px;
  display: flex;
  gap: 10px;
}
.switch-qs {
  position: relative;
}
.switch-qs-content {
  display: none;
  position: absolute;
  background: white;
  min-height: 100px;
  border: 1px solid var(--fade-border);
  padding: 16px;
  border-radius: 8px; 
  top: 0;
  min-width: 265px;
  font-size: 14px;
  transform: translate(-50%, -100%);
  left: 50%;
  cursor: pointer;
  font-size: 12px;
  line-height: 20px;
  z-index: 9;
}
.switch-qs:hover .switch-qs-content{
  display: block;
}
span.qs-span {
  width: 32px;
  background: #F6F6F6;
  padding: 3px 4px 5px;
  border-radius: 50px;
  display: inline-flex;
  justify-content: center;
  cursor: pointer;
}
.spf-switch-wrap {
  background: #F6F6F6;
  padding: 4px;
  border-radius: 50px;
  display: inline-flex;
  width: 56px;
    height: 32px;
}
.spf-switch-wrap a {
  width: 100px;
  text-align: center;
  border-radius: 50px;
}
.spf-switch-wrap a.active{
  background: white;
}
.spf-switch-wrap a span {
  margin-top: -1px;
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: 1px;
}
@media only screen and (max-width: 990px) {
  .switch-qs-content {
    transform: translate(-100%, -100%);
    /* left: 100%; */
    left: 300%;
  }
}
.spf-switch-wrap.active {
  background: #2CD151;
}
.spf-switch-outerwrap > .base.normal {
  line-height: 16px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
}
.withSPF25{
  padding-bottom: 2px;
  /* display: none; */
}
</style>
{% assign link = "" %}
{% if product.handle contains '-spf' %}
  {% assign link = product.handle | replace: '-spf', '' %}
{% else %}
  {% assign link = product.handle | append: '-spf' %}
{% endif %}
<div class="spf-switch-outerwrap">
  <div class="spf-switch-wrap {% if product.handle contains '-spf' %}active{% endif %}">
    <a href="/products/{{ link }}" class="base normal {% unless product.handle contains '-spf' %}active{% endunless %}">
      <span>
        <!-- No SPF -->
      </span>
    </a>
    <a href="/products/{{ link }}" class="base normal {% if product.handle contains '-spf' %}active{% endif %}">
      <span>
        <!-- SPF -->
      </span>
    </a>
  </div>
  <div class="base normal">With SPF<span class="withSPF25">25</span></div>
  <div class="switch-qs">
    <span class="qs-span">
      ?
    </span>
    <div class="switch-qs-content">
      <p>SPF (Sun Protection Factor), measures how well a lip balm protects your lips from the sun's harmful UV rays. SPF25 blocks about 96% of UVB rays, significantly reducing the risk of sunburn and long-term skin damage.</p>
      <br><p>The taste and smell of our SPF balms arenâ€™t different from the normal balms and Honeybalm SPF can be identified by the SPF logo on the back of each balm.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
{% endunless %}
{% endif %}